query: The attached file contains a list of vendors in the Liminal Springs mall, along with each vendor’s monthly revenue and the rent they pay the mall. I want you to find the vendor that makes the least money, relative to the rent it pays. Then, tell me what is listed in the “type” column for that vendor.

tasks.description: Извлечь данные о доходах и арендной плате для каждого продавца.
Вычислить соотношение дохода к арендной плате для каждого продавца.
Определить продавца с наименьшим соотношением дохода к арендной плате.

assumptions: All revenue and rent figures are accurate and represent the same time period.
The ratio of revenue to rent is calculated as Revenue / Rent.
reasoning_steps: Extract revenue and rent data for each seller from the provided document.
Calculate the revenue-to-rent ratio for each seller.
Identify the seller with the lowest revenue-to-rent ratio.
conclusions: The seller with the lowest revenue-to-rent ratio is identified as the one with the least financial efficiency in terms of income generated relative to rent paid.
proposed_answer_outline: Calculate the revenue-to-rent ratio for each seller.
List the ratios and identify the minimum.
Provide the name and details of the seller with the lowest ratio.
